# Next Testing Stack

- Standard stack: Vitest with React Testing Library and `jsdom` for unit and integration tests, plus Playwright for end-to-end tests.
- In TypeScript Next.js apps with path aliases, include `vite-tsconfig-paths` in the Vitest config.
- Prefer package scripts over one-off package runners so commands stay Bun-native and repeatable.
- Use these dependency defaults when bootstrapping a Next.js app:
  - `bun add -D vitest @vitejs/plugin-react jsdom @testing-library/react @testing-library/dom vite-tsconfig-paths`
  - `bun add -D @playwright/test`
- Add scripts similar to:

```json
{
  "test": "vitest run",
  "test:watch": "vitest",
  "test:e2e": "playwright test",
  "test:all": "bun run test && bun run test:e2e",
  "playwright:install": "playwright install"
}
```

- Run browser installation through the script: `bun run playwright:install`
- For async Server Components or full tenant routing validation, prefer Playwright over Vitest.
